title: For Sale:   Colt 1903 Pocket Hammerless 1 Family 2 Generation
location: Sparta, NC 28675, North Carolina, United States
postcontent: Colt Model 1903 Pocket Hammerless .32 Caliber Automatic. Serial #:218137. Manufactured in 1916. Condition Very Good/95%+. I am Tom Klein, a former Curios & Relics licensee who has enjoyed seriously collecting quality firearms for over 40 years. When I reached retirement age with my passion for guns unabated, instead of sitting back in my rocking chair I upgraded to full blown FFL and established Heritage Arms LLC, located at 68 N. Main St., Sparta, NC., 28675. Heritage Arms specializes in Collectible and high quality pre-owned firearms. I purchase 1 gun or 100+ guns. Private and estate collections large and small. This Colt Model 1903 and a Colt Model 1908 (auctioning simultaneously) came to me this past week from an 80 year old gentleman who is gradually liquidating his father’s collection he inherited some 25 years ago. I have acquired severaI fine firearms from him over the past year and a half and have yet to receive one from that collection that was in less than 95% condition. The detailed photos speak for themselves. His father knew a fine gun. The only real flaw of any concern I can point out is a crack in the right hand grip that probably occurred by over tightening the screw. I have not removed the grips. However it does not appear to have cracked through into two pieces since it is not loose. In fact, it took me awhile before I even noticed it. This Colt has been in one family for two generations and I am pleased to be able to pass a classic along, perhaps to a younger generation collector who will also enjoy and care for it for many years to come. During the auction this Colt will be available for purchase in my Heritage Arms Store. If it sells the auction will be immediately terminated.
